&lt;h2&gt;🧰 &lt;strong&gt;Who We Are&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Wakam is a &lt;strong&gt;B2B2C insurance company&lt;/strong&gt; that creates &lt;strong&gt;white-label insurance solutions&lt;/strong&gt; via its &lt;strong&gt;Play&amp;amp;Plug®&lt;/strong&gt; technology platform for more than &lt;strong&gt;80 partners&lt;/strong&gt;. We provide most of our insurance products through &lt;strong&gt;APIs&lt;/strong&gt; and operate across &lt;strong&gt;32 countries&lt;/strong&gt;, making Wakam the &lt;strong&gt;European leader in digital and embedded insurance&lt;/strong&gt;. Wakam is also a &lt;strong&gt;mission-driven company&lt;/strong&gt; dedicated to &lt;strong&gt;&quot;enabling transparent and impactful insurance.&quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;🚀 &lt;strong&gt;About the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the &lt;strong&gt;Partnerships Control team&lt;/strong&gt;, which plays a critical role for:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;policyholders&lt;/strong&gt;, by ensuring that partners deliver reliable, high-quality service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Our&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;regulators in France and across Europe&lt;/strong&gt;, by demonstrating robust oversight of delegated activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Controls cover distribution and management of insurance products, risk identification and assessment, and regulatory compliance (e.g. AM, IDD, GDPR).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To support a &lt;strong&gt;temporary reinforcement of our perimeter&lt;/strong&gt;, we are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Partnership Controller (6-month fixed-term contract)&lt;/strong&gt; with strong expertise in &lt;strong&gt;claims management and compliance&lt;/strong&gt;. You will report to the &lt;strong&gt;Partnership Control Team Lead&lt;/strong&gt; and work closely with operational teams, Compliance, Legal, and external partners.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;🎯&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Your Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a &lt;strong&gt;Partnership Controller&lt;/strong&gt;, your mission is to assess and challenge how our partners manage delegated insurance activities. You will ensure they:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;high standard of service&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;to our policyholders, particularly in&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;claims handling&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Operate within a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;robust risk and compliance framework&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Align with&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Wakam&#39;s expectations, procedures, and regulatory obligations&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be involved in the &lt;strong&gt;control cycle&lt;/strong&gt; from preparation to follow-up.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;📆 &lt;strong&gt;Your Day-to-Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Prepare and Organise Controls&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organise controls in line with the annual&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;control plan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;preparation phase&lt;/strong&gt;: contractual review, claims portfolio analysis, definition of control scope and objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;round-table meetings with internal stakeholders&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;(Claims, Operations, Compliance, Legal, etc.) to identify risks and to collect expectations,and feedback on the partner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Conduct Controls (Remote)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform controls with partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assess the&amp;nbsp;operational &lt;strong&gt;handling framework&lt;/strong&gt;: processes, timelines, customer communication and complaint management…&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;sample reviews and quality checks&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;on files, focusing on accuracy, consistency, and regulatory and contractual compliance.&lt;/li&g

&lt;h2&gt;🚀 About the Team&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Motor Pricing team&lt;/strong&gt;, which supports Wakam’s partner portfolios by delivering&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;technical pricing excellence&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;profitability steering&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The team works in close collaboration with stakeholders across&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Risk, Reinsurance, Data, Underwriting, and Partner Management&lt;/strong&gt;, and plays a key role in ensuring our Motor business remains&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;sustainable, competitive, and scalable&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;across markets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;🎯 Your Mission&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Motor Pricing Actuary&lt;/strong&gt;, you will deliver pricing and portfolio analysis work across the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;UK and rest of Europe scope (excluding France)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your core objective is to&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;secure profitability&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;and strengthen&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;technical portfolio management&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;through robust pricing, performance monitoring, and actionable recommendations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will operate with a high level of autonomy, taking ownership of projects&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;end-to-end&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;— from analysis and recommendation to deliverables ready for committee review and implementation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;✏️ Your Responsibilities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;End-to-End Pricing &amp;amp; Portfolio Projects&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will independently manage projects covering:&lt;/p&gt;
